						               													<description>The game is played with 12 treasure tiles and a six-sided die. The front of the tiles show various treasures: crown, genie lamp, or goblet. Each tile has one, two, or three treasures of the same type. To start the game, all twelve tiles are placed face down in the playing area.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Three faces of the die show a crown, lamp, and goblet; the other three show the numbers one, two, and three. Players take turns rolling the die, then must turn over a tile with either the same type of treasure (if a treasure was rolled) or the matching number of treasures (if a number was rolled). If the treasure matches, the player keeps it and places it face down in front of her.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Instead of turning over a tile in the center of the playing area, the active player may turn over a tile belonging to an opponent. If the tile matches, the player may steal it and take it into her own area.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
